## taskboard — Task Management with Workflow Graphs

Base URL: http://127.0.0.1:8768/api
All responses are plain text.

### Your workflow
1. Check your tasks: GET /api/my-tasks?agent=YOUR_ID
2. Start a task: POST /api/ticket/<tid>/node/<nid>/start {"agent":"YOUR_ID"}
3. Complete checklist items: POST /api/ticket/<tid>/node/<nid>/check/<idx> {"agent":"YOUR_ID"}
4. Complete the node: POST /api/ticket/<tid>/node/<nid>/complete {"agent":"YOUR_ID"}
5. For decision nodes: POST /api/ticket/<tid>/node/<nid>/decide {"agent":"YOUR_ID","decision":"yes|no"}
6. Add worklog notes: POST /api/ticket/<tid>/worklog {"agent":"YOUR_ID","content":"..."}

### Endpoints

GET  /api/health — returns 'ok'
GET  /api/my-tasks?agent=ID — your ready/active tasks across all tickets
GET  /api/tickets — list all tickets (?status=active&type=bug&priority=high)
GET  /api/ticket/<id> — ticket detail with current position
GET  /api/ticket/<id>/graph — full graph with node statuses
GET  /api/ticket/<id>/worklog — worklog entries
GET  /api/templates — list workflow templates
GET  /api/template/<id> — template detail with nodes and edges
GET  /api/roles — agent-to-role mappings
GET  /api/process-issues — process issues (?status=open)

POST /api/ticket/<tid>/node/<nid>/start {"agent":"ID"}
POST /api/ticket/<tid>/node/<nid>/check/<idx> {"agent":"ID"}
POST /api/ticket/<tid>/node/<nid>/complete {"agent":"ID"}
POST /api/ticket/<tid>/node/<nid>/decide {"agent":"ID","decision":"CHOICE"}
POST /api/ticket/<tid>/node/<nid>/skip {"agent":"ID","reason":"..."}
POST /api/ticket/<tid>/node/<nid>/escalate-respond {"agent":"operator","response":"..."}
POST /api/ticket/<tid>/worklog {"agent":"ID","content":"..."}
POST /api/ticket/create {"template_id":"...","title":"...","priority":"high","created_by":"ID"}
POST /api/process-issue {"issue_type":"process_gap","title":"...","description":"...","reported_by":"ID"}
POST /api/role/assign {"agent_id":"ID","role":"coder"}

### Conventions
- Check /api/my-tasks periodically to see if you have work
- Always complete ALL checklist items before completing a node
- Skipping a node logs a VIOLATION — only do this with team consensus
- Use worklog to document your progress and findings
- Report process issues if instructions are unclear or workflow has gaps
